<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - REASSEMBLE -
        REMOTE CONTROL ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13014_8.xml" xrefid="f1301402">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new key in the rod and bracket assembly and install into the remote housing,
                sliding shift finger (inner) on the end of the rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Line up set screw hole and install set screw. Tighten to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install joint shift rod through the cross holes and through the outer finger, making sure
                the finger is inserted into the bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align set screw hole and install set screw. Tighten to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install end cover and secure with four bolts and lockwashers. Tighten to 34 to 41 ft-lbs.
                (46 to 56 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two new oil seals in the joint shift rod bores.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install joint assembly and secure with set screw.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
